Defendant Daniel R Vachalek in court with attorney Robert Courtney for  David John Molter.  Ted S. Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea Colloquy.
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.   Penalty enhancer struck by Court upon motion of the State.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

60 Days Huber (Credit - 0 days) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.

Term of Probation:  12 Months

Conditions of Probation:
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
-Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  40 hours of community service by December 18, 2015
- Maintain valid driver's license;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Complete an Anger Management and Victim Impact Course;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment.

Costs: $243.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
To be paid today.  Failure to pay 4 days Huber as a contempt.

Condition Time: 15 days  Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - Stayed and to be used at the agent's discretion.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
